{#
  Walkthrough Landing Page
  FixMyStreet citizen problem reporting platform
#}

<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Try FixMyStreet</h1>

<div class="govuk-panel govuk-panel--confirmation ndx-walkthrough-value-prop">
  <h2 class="govuk-panel__title">
    See how a citizen reporting platform works in 20 minutes
  </h2>
  <div class="govuk-panel__body">
    Experience FixMyStreet with 260 realistic demo reports across Camden. Report a problem, explore the council dashboard, and understand the architecture.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="govuk-inset-text ndx-walkthrough-reassurance">
  <strong class="govuk-!-font-size-24">No technical knowledge required</strong>
  <p class="govuk-body">
    This walkthrough guides you step-by-step through the citizen and council experience.
    You will browse a map, submit a report, and explore an admin dashboard.
    Perfect for service managers, councillors, and anyone evaluating citizen engagement tools.
  </p>
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What you'll do</h2>

<p class="govuk-body-l">
  In this 20-minute walkthrough, you'll:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Find your credentials</strong> - Get the FixMyStreet URL and admin login from CloudFormation (2 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Explore the citizen view</strong> - Browse the map, search by postcode, and view existing reports (3 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Report a problem</strong> - Submit a new report as a citizen with location, category, and description (4 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>View the council dashboard</strong> - Sign in as council admin and see all reports on a map (3 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Explore the admin panel</strong> - Browse report statistics and manage reports from the admin perspective (3 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Understand the architecture</strong> - Review the AWS infrastructure powering the platform (2 minutes)
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="ndx-walkthrough-prerequisites">
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Before you start</h2>

  <div class="govuk-warning-text">
    <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
    <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
      <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Important</span>
      You must have already deployed the FixMyStreet scenario via NDX:Try.
    </strong>
  </div>

  <p class="govuk-body">
    <a href="/scenarios/fixmystreet/" class="govuk-link">Deploy the FixMyStreet scenario</a> if you haven't already.
    Deployment takes 15 to 20 minutes.
  </p>
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What you'll learn</h2>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">For service managers</h3>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>How residents report problems to their council</li>
      <li>The council dashboard for managing and prioritising reports</li>
      <li>How categories and statuses help triage street issues</li>
      <li>Potential for reducing phone-based reporting</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">For technical staff</h3>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Container-based architecture on AWS Fargate</li>
      <li>PostgreSQL with PostGIS for geospatial data</li>
      <li>CloudFront for HTTPS and global caching</li>
      <li>EFS for persistent photo storage</li>
      <li>OpenStreetMap integration for mapping</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

